         <abstract>
            <p>We show, for each $n \geq 1$, that the $(2n + 1)$-point Kronrod extension of the $n$-point Gaussian quadrature formula for the measure $$d\sigma_\gamma(t) = (1 + \gamma)^2(1 - t^2)^{1/2}dt/((1 + \gamma)^2 - 4\gamma t^2),\quad -1 &lt; \gamma \leq 1,$$ has the properties that its $n + 1$ Kronrod nodes interlace with the $n$ Gauss nodes and all its $2n + 1$ weights are positive. We also produce explicit formulae for the weights.</p>
          </abstract>
